(437, 1, 'textarea', 'Описание', 'Блок 1', 23, 3, 0, 'If you want to sell on our marketplace yourself, please fill out the application. If you would like to cooperate as a supplier, please see the information below.'),
(438, 1, 'textarea', 'Заголовок', 'Блок 2', 23, 1, 0, ''),
(439, 1, 'ckeditor', 'Описание', 'Блок 2', 23, 2, 0, '<h3>For product groups presented on the site</h3><p>To start cooperation, you must provide the following information:</p><ul><li>A brief description of the brand, its share in percentage and money among product and price analogues in the market.</li><li>Quarterly turnover for previous periods in various types of sales (online, offline, wholesale).</li><li>Estimated turnover taking into account seasonality.</li><li>Marketing fund for brand development on the part of the supplier and the Brand.</li></ul><h3>For groups of goods not presented on the site</h3><p>To start cooperation, you must provide the following information:</p><ul><li>A brief description of the brand, its share in percentage and money among product and price analogues in the market.</li><li>Quarterly turnover for previous periods in various types of sales (online, offline, wholesale).</li><li>Estimated turnover taking into account seasonality.</li><li>Marketing fund for brand development on the part of the supplier and the Brand.</li></ul><h3>We use the finest selection of ingredients to create our products that are a combination of tradition and modernism</h3><p>Sweets are produced from prepared semi-finished products - candy masses, icing, finishing materials. From the candy masses, candy bodies are first made, which are then glazed or subjected to other processing. Methods for obtaining cases are different depending on the structural and mechanical properties of the candy masses.<br>The main types of raw materials for the production of sweets are:</p><ul><li>granulated sugar;</li><li>starch syrup;</li><li>bee honey;</li><li>fruits and berries;</li><li>cocoa beans;</li><li>nuts (hazelnuts, almonds, cashews, etc).</li></ul><p>Candy production technology includes the following main stages: preparation of raw materials, preparation of semi-finished products to obtain candy mass; preparation of candy mass, molding of candy bodies; structure formation of candy bodies; finishing of candy cases, including glazing; candy packaging.<br><br>Hot liquid candy masses are cast into molds, where, upon cooling and standing, they acquire a structure of sufficient mechanical strength. Forms are stamped in trays filled with starch or granulated sugar. After curing, the body of sweets is freed from the molding material. Sufficiently viscous masses are smeared or rolled into a layer, which is then cut into individual candies. Thick masses are pressed out in the form of bundles. Light masses are formed by jigging.<br>Sweets are glazed mainly with chocolate icing.</p>'),
