(103, 1, 'ckeditor', 'Описание', 'Блок 4', 5, 2, 0, '<p>Sweets are produced from prepared semi-finished products - candy masses, icing, finishing materials. From the candy masses, candy bodies are first made, which are then glazed or subjected to other processing. Methods for obtaining cases are different depending on the structural and mechanical properties of the candy masses.<br>The main types of raw materials for the production of sweets are:</p><ul><li>granulated sugar;</li><li>starch syrup;</li><li>bee honey;</li><li>fruits and berries;</li><li>cocoa beans;</li><li>nuts (hazelnuts, almonds, cashews, etc).</li></ul><p>Candy production technology includes the following main stages: preparation of raw materials, preparation of semi-finished products to obtain candy mass; preparation of candy mass, molding of candy bodies; structure formation of candy bodies; finishing of candy cases, including glazing; candy packaging.<br><br>Hot liquid candy masses are cast into molds, where, upon cooling and standing, they acquire a structure of sufficient mechanical strength. Forms are stamped in trays filled with starch or granulated sugar. After curing, the body of sweets is freed from the molding material. Sufficiently viscous masses are smeared or rolled into a layer, which is then cut into individual candies. Thick masses are pressed out in the form of bundles. Light masses are formed by jigging.<br>Sweets are glazed mainly with chocolate icing.</p>'),
